In January 2017, the Company announced the execution of a 20-year power purchase agreement and two 15-year power purchase agreements with the CFE, for the sale of the energy generated by the 100 MWAC Tepezalé Solar project to be located in the State onguascalientes, The agreements include 20 years for the clean energy certiﬁcates and 15 years for the capacity, The Tepezalé Solar project will be developed and constructed by the Company in collaboration with Trina Solar (NYSE: TSL), a world leader in solar energy, who will have a 10% interest in the project, The company expects that the Tepezalé Solar project will start commercial operations in the second quarter of 2019 and have estimated investment of approximately USD$100 million,
